  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &gt;18

          -  Child's A or B cirrhosis

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Informed consent not available

          -  Presence of portal vein thrombosis, portal vein tumor thrombus, or previous portal
             vein embolisation

          -  Presence of hepatic artery thrombosis, previous transarterial therapy like TACE,
             lipiodol-ethanol mixture injection or transarterial internal radiation

          -  Anticipation of portal vein resection

          -  Emergency hepatectomy

          -  Ruptured HCC

          -  Adhesion or anatomical variation that preclude safe and successful application of
             Pringle maneuver

          -  Anticipation of concomitant bowel or bile duct resection
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
